<font color="#FF0000">DOING WHAT YOU THINK IS RIGHT</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jul 30 18:38:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I think we each need to be strong enough to do what we think is right.  Because of how we are brought up and live, women have a unique perspective.  It is time to share our opinions and needs with the world and to be heard.  <br><br>
In a way, we have to do this in our own homes.  Home is not a place to be silent about what is important to us.  Maybe for Raelene, moving to a home that made sense to her meant she was in a place where she could do things in the way she thought was right.
